Higher education institutions in the [[United Arab Emirates]] need to be recognized by the Commission for Academic Accreditation (CAA), which is part of the [[Ministry of Education (United Arab Emirates)|Ministry of Education]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.caa.ae/caa/DesktopDefault.aspx|title=CAA Portal|website=www.caa.ae|access-date=2018-04-04}}</ref> The Ministry of Education does not recognize educational institutions based in [[List of free-trade zones in the United Arab Emirates|free zones]]. While individual [[Emirates of the United Arab Emirates|Emirates]] are responsible for managing the standards of educational institutions within their free zones, [[Emirate of Dubai|Dubai]] is the only Emirate that does so through the [[Knowledge and Human Development Authority|Knowledge and Human Development Authority's]] University Quality Assurance International Board. Ras Al Khaimah is currently working on tightening rules and regulations that govern higher academic institutions in the Emirate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenational.ae/uae/education/rak-tightens-rules-for-free-zone-universities-1.88948|title=RAK tightens rules for free zone universities|work=The National|access-date=2018-04-04|language=en}}</ref>
