{{Infobox official post |post = Ministry of National Education |insignia = Coat of arms of Romania.svg |insigniasize = 150px |insigniacaption = Coat of arms of Romania |image = |imagesize = 120px |incumbent = [[Ecaterina Andronescu]] |incumbentsince = 20 November 2018 |formation = |first = [[Spiru Haret]] |website = [http://www.edu.ro/ www.mects.ro] }}
The '''Ministry of National Education''' (Romanian: ''Ministerul Educației Naționale)'' is one of the ministries of the [[Government of Romania]].<ref>{{ro}} [http://www.edu.ro www.edu.ro] - official site</ref>
==Former names of the Ministry== Over the years the Ministry changed its title. Initially it was called '''Ministry of Religion and Public Instruction''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Religiei și Instrucțiunii Publice}}), then '''Ministryof Public Instruction''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Instrucţiunii Publice}}), then it changed to '''Ministry of Teaching''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Învǎțǎmântului}}), '''Ministry of Teaching and Science''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Învǎțǎmântului și Științei}}), than changed back to '''Ministry of Teaching''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Învǎțǎmântului}}). When [[Andrei Marga]] became Minister, it introduced the largest reform measures, starting with the name of the institution: '''Ministry of National Education''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Educației Naționale}}). In 2000 the name was changed to '''Ministry of Education and Research''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Educației și Cercetǎrii}}). This title was kept until April 2007, when it changed to '''Ministry of Education, Research and Youth''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Educației, Cercetǎrii și Tineretului}}). In 21 December 2012 the title was changed to '''Ministry of National Education''' ({{lang-ro|Ministerul Educației Naționale}}) and was kept until 17 December 2014, when it changed to '''Ministry of National Education and Scientific Research''' (Romanian: ''Ministerul Educaței Naționale și Cercetării Științifice'') This title was kept until 4 January 2017, when it changed back to '''Ministry of National Education.'''
